eqlAccessGroupTable.name: eqlAccessGroupTable
eqlAccessGroupTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table stores information for both access records and access groups. This MIB table uses the same object to describe both. Whether the object is an Access Group or Access Record is described by its eqlAccessGroupType field. TimeoutDelete:90

eqlAccessGroupEntry.name: eqlAccessGroupEntry
eqlAccessGroupEntry.description: An entry in the Access Group table.

eqlAccessGroupIndex.name: eqlAccessGroupIndex
eqlAccessGroupIndex.description: The index of the access group.

eqlAccessGroupRowStatus.name: eqlAccessGroupRowStatus
eqlAccessGroupRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row.

eqlAccessGroupUUID.name: eqlAccessGroupUUID
eqlAccessGroupUUID.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides the UUID of the VMWare host used to create the Access Group. The description can be up to 63 characters plus NULL.

eqlAccessGroupName.name: eqlAccessGroupName
eqlAccessGroupName.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides the name of the access group. The description can be up to 31 characters plus NULL.

eqlAccessGroupKeyName.name: eqlAccessGroupKeyName
eqlAccessGroupKeyName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies the iSCSI profile sysprep version of eqlAccessGroupName. It is populated by the backend on a row-create.

eqlAccessGroupDescription.name: eqlAccessGroupDescription
eqlAccessGroupDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details of the access group. The description can be up to 127 characters plus NULL.

eqlAccessGroupAdminKey.name: eqlAccessGroupAdminKey
eqlAccessGroupAdminKey.description: This field specifies the unique key for identifying the administrator who owns this access group.

eqlAccessGroupType.name: eqlAccessGroupType
eqlAccessGroupType.description: This field describes whether the ACL is an access group or access record.

eqlAccessGroupPrivacyFlag.name: eqlAccessGroupPrivacyFlag
eqlAccessGroupPrivacyFlag.description: This field is used to mark if an access group is public (able to be used by any user) or private (only able to be used by the person who created it or group admin).

eqlAccessGroupByTypeTable.name: eqlAccessGroupByTypeTable
eqlAccessGroupByTypeTable.description: Equallogic-Dynamic This table displays information for access records and access groups, like eqlAccessGroupTable, but partitioned by type (access-record, access-group), which is part of the index (eqlAccessGroupType).

eqlAccessGroupByTypeEntry.name: eqlAccessGroupByTypeEntry
eqlAccessGroupByTypeEntry.description: An entry in the Access Group By Type table.

eqlAccessGroupByTypeUUID.name: eqlAccessGroupByTypeUUID
eqlAccessGroupByTypeUUID.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides the UUID of the VMWare host used to create the Access Group. The description can be up to 63 characters plus NULL.

eqlAccessGroupByTypeName.name: eqlAccessGroupByTypeName
eqlAccessGroupByTypeName.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides the name of the access group. The description can be up to 31 characters plus NULL.

eqlAccessGroupByTypeDescription.name: eqlAccessGroupByTypeDescription
eqlAccessGroupByTypeDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details of the access group. The description can be up to 127 characters plus NULL.

eqlAccessGroupByTypeAdminKey.name: eqlAccessGroupByTypeAdminKey
eqlAccessGroupByTypeAdminKey.description: This field specifies the unique key for identifying an access group.

eqlAccessGroupMemberTable.name: eqlAccessGroupMemberTable
eqlAccessGroupMemberTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table represents a hierarchy of access groups via their corresonding eqlAccessGroupIndex in the eqlAccessGroupTable.

eqlAccessGroupMemberEntry.name: eqlAccessGroupMemberEntry
eqlAccessGroupMemberEntry.description: An entry in the Access Group Member table.

eqlAccessGroupChildIndex.name: eqlAccessGroupChildIndex
eqlAccessGroupChildIndex.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The eqlAccessGroupIndex in the eqlAccessGroupTable of the host access group which is associated with a cluster access group, which is defined by the index represented in eqlAccessGroupIndex of the full table index.

eqlAccessGroupMemberRowStatus.name: eqlAccessGroupMemberRowStatus
eqlAccessGroupMemberRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row.

eqlAccessPointTable.name: eqlAccessPointTable
eqlAccessPointTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table stores stores information on all the configured access points. One row for each access point that the PS-Admin creates.

eqlAccessPointEntry.name: eqlAccessPointEntry
eqlAccessPointEntry.description: An entry in the Access Point Table.

eqlAccessPointIndex.name: eqlAccessPointIndex
eqlAccessPointIndex.description: The index of the access point.

eqlAccessPointRowStatus.name: eqlAccessPointRowStatus
eqlAccessPointRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row.

eqlAccessPointInitiatorName.name: eqlAccessPointInitiatorName
eqlAccessPointInitiatorName.description: The name of the iscsi initiator permitted to discover or login.

eqlAccessPointInitiatorCHAPUserName.name: eqlAccessPointInitiatorCHAPUserName
eqlAccessPointInitiatorCHAPUserName.description: The 256 byte character name user name to be used for initiator authentication.

eqlAccessPointDescription.name: eqlAccessPointDescription
eqlAccessPointDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details of the access group. The description can be up to 127 characters plus NULL.

eqlAccessPointAddrTable.name: eqlAccessPointAddrTable
eqlAccessPointAddrTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table stores stores information on all the configured access points. One row for each access point that the PS-Admin creates.

eqlAccessPointAddrEntry.name: eqlAccessPointAddrEntry
eqlAccessPointAddrEntry.description: An entry in the Access Point IP Address Table.

eqlAccessPointAddrIndex.name: eqlAccessPointAddrIndex
eqlAccessPointAddrIndex.description: The index of the access point IP Address table.

eqlAccessPointAddrRowStatus.name: eqlAccessPointAddrRowStatus
eqlAccessPointAddrRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row.

eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddrType.name: eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddrType
eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddrType.description: The IP version of the address of the initiator and corresponding wildcard allowed to access the target.

eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddr.name: eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddr
eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddr.description: The IP address of the initiator allowed to access the target.

eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddrWildcardT.name: eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddrWildcardType
eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddrWildcardT.description: The IP version of the address of the initiator and corresponding wildcard allowed to access the target.

eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddrWildcard.name: eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddrWildcard
eqlAccessPointAddrInitiatorAddrWildcard.description: The wildcard mask defines which portion of the eqlInitiatorAddress that does not have to match for the initiator to be permitted access to the volume. Type IPv4 mask is expressed in the form x.x.x.x, where x is 255 or 0. When x is 255, then that portion of the initiator's ip address must match. When x is 0, then that portion of the initiator's ip address does not have to match.

eqlAccessGroupObjectAssocCreator.name: eqlAccessGroupObjectAssocCreator
